<br>
&quot;1/ Economy is not governed by fate, like free market zealots would like to believe.Things can change, and will.&quot;<br>
<br>
Free market zealots? LOL.... Ok, why do you say that capitalists say a nations economy is governed by fate? Isnt that an oxymoron? Isnt capitalism based upon the premise that we dont wait for fate, that we do things to ensure success? Tell me, where would we be without a free market? Do you really think the world would be better? What is your alternate option to a free market society? A government controlled market? It didn't work in the USSR. I doubt if it will any where else. Can you give me an example of a non-free market society that works?<br>
<br>
&quot;3/People often attack America when its about to criticize capitalism: its because Capitalism and USA are bound together, a tool for each other if you want.&quot; <br>
<br>
I really don't understand your logic here. How are they bound together? In fact, isnt the GNP of the European union outstripping the GNP of the USA? Why arent you crying out against Europe? How dare they, those dirty imperialist Europeans!  LOL<br>
<br>
&quot;As people realise its time to really limit free market before its too late (you know, those little things like global warming and world great poverty, beeing worse and worse every day, but hey isnt it destiny?  ), they are also conscious they will have to find a way and limit USA imperialism....because capitalism and USA are tied together.&quot;<br>
<br>
Do you seriously blame the &quot;free market&quot; for world poverty and global warming? How absurd. Where are your facts? How can one nation, or even a group of nations, which operates within a free market cause or keep any other nation or group of nations in poverty? Do you seriously believe that global warming would not exist if the free market system did not? How naive. It might even be worse. Give me some examples of American imperialism? I would dearly love to hear them. One thing alot of people like you fail to remember is that<br>
Americans are probably the most generous people in the world. No other country's citizens give more to charitable causes ... and not all of those charities benefit only Americans. Much of it goes to people that need it around the world.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think free market in Europe has reached its limits, or the limits people are ready to pay for, things are changing, we are not going to sell our identity in the name of Ideology.&quot;<br>
<br>
Very funny. The Europen market continues to grow. They will soon, without a doubt, be the dominant economic power. Sell your identity in the name of ideology? What do you mean by this? Won't you be doing the same thing in this &quot;non-free market everyone is equal&quot; way of life you seem to favor?<br>
<br>
&quot;4/ Sadly, the real evil axis nowadays, is not the one we can find in newspapers: Its Washington/WTO/IMF.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is funny in the extreme. I have never really understood the arguments against the world WTO or IMF. Can you explain why they are bad? Seriously, can you give me a logical argument? How can an organization that promotes world trade and another that helps countries that are in financial crisis be evil? Do you really know what they do?<br>
<br>
&quot;5/ 09/11 Bombing were tragics, but they dont allow USA to do whatever, nor do we have to live forever sentenced to think, read, and sleep 09/11.&quot;<br>
<br>
Where are you from? Do you think it was just Americans killed on 9/11? What do you consider the USA &quot;doing whatever?&quot; Are we the only country engaged in the fight against terrorism? Have you been blind and deaf to all of the other terrorism that has happened at an increased rate, world wide, since 9-11? Do you truly believe that none of this other terrorism would have happened if Americans had not taken such a strong stand against it? Are you willing to let your friends, neighbors, and loved ones be killed and then do nothing to stop it just because it might create trouble for a while?<br>
<br>
Please, if you are going to make statements like these, at least put facts down instead of just opinion and supposition.<br>
<br>
I will hazard a few guesses here. You are probably young, maybe old enough to just be starting college, maybe not. Chances are you are not an American. You are full of angst and anger. You do not like your life situation, or possibly that of your families.You do not like the situation our world is in either ( not that any of us do) and are frustrated because the really bad things dont seem to be getting corrected. And, without really studying to see the whole picture, you have latched on an extreme point of view about the causes. Why, because it is easy to do. You probably did not form these opinions on your own. Most likely someone else told you these things and you accepted them because you dont like your lot in life and want someone to blame.<br>
<br>
I know this will probably cause a flurry of responses. I guess we will see what happens. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elladin>Elladin</A> at: 1/24/03 8:07:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=belarkan>Belarkan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 8:42:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Idiot capitalists</span><hr size=1> I wont answer on personal attacks, but if you honestly want to know why one would think like me (im not the only one, by far, so *boggle*, i invite you to read here, and maybe leave behind most of your generally accepted ideas.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
1/ About the IMF and WTO and the so called free market:<br>
<br>
-from Pierre Bourdieu, sociolog and Philosopher:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.analitica.com/bitblioteca/bourdieu/neoliberalism.asp">www.analitica.com/bitblio...ralism.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
How those organisations, rather than helping poor countries, have actually ruined them (see those areas where IMF has enforced its prescriptions, Africa, South America, all those countries are wasted, worse than before.<br>
<br>
-&quot;Globalization and Its Discontents&quot;, by Joseph e. Stiglitz, nobel prize winner, professor of economics at Columbia University.<br>
You can have a sample here, its talking about Ethiopia and IMF.<br>
<br>
Im sure youll be stuned, unless of course you just want to flamme:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.wwnorton.com/catalog/spring02/005124excerpt.htm">www.wwnorton.com/catalog/...xcerpt.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
-&quot;Rethinking globalisation&quot;, by Martin Khor, Director of the Third World Network, a clearly biased organisation, but one would be biased against WTO for less than that.<br>
<br>
How WTO has become the main tool for International enterprises to increase their power.<br>
<br>
Read here if you dont want to read the whole book:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.jubilee2000uk.org/analysis/book_review/Martin%20khor.htm">www.jubilee2000uk.org/ana...20khor.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
2/ How free market and Globalisation (its consequence) is slowly depriving politics over the world, of any real power, through illegal organisations such as WTO and IMF? Illegal, thats obvious, because they have no legitimacy as far as people vote goes.<br>
They operate across borders.<br>
Thats why i made my comment about economy slowly turning into fate, something you cant change, because you hold no power on it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
3/Now about global warming: <br>
So, you dont see the link between free market, economic globalisation, and Global Warming? (obviously, i was also talking about all ecologic issues, basiccaly we are destroying our planet.)<br>
Ill tell you that: as ultra-liberalism (thats how we call globalisation policy in france) makes its way into minds (not all minds, fear not), people are thinking more about making money, and our planet is the last of their concerns.<br>
But...isnt it a matter of life or death?<br>
<br>
You could read here, as a start if you want (youll note the nice attitude of USA on this matter).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.econ.yale.edu/~nordhaus/homepage/nordhaus_science_110901.pdf">www.econ.yale.edu/~nordha...110901.pdf</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://mondediplo.com/2002/08/01edito?var_s=warming">mondediplo.com/2002/08/01..._s=warming</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
4/ About USA &quot;charity&quot;, lets pass on your cliche, anyway all western countries are guilty.<br>
You must understand that charity, this old religious concept, is only helping us to get rid of our guilt.In fact it helps to maintain a whole system, so we dont have to find real organised solutions.To assist is not to help.<br>
<br>
Again, in aid for developpement, US are the worst students of the class; a class of donkeys, ill agree.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.globalissues.org/TradeRelated/Debt/USAid.asp">www.globalissues.org/Trad.../USAid.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
You may also want to have a look at EOCD for more numbers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.oecd.org/">www.oecd.org/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
/5 Terrorism.<br>
<br>
*Schrug* I was trying to get an answer, how is Irak in any way related to terrorism (Bombings by Al Quaeda), but all i seem to get are hysteric answers.<br>
AL Qaeda is a whole different matter, but most people seem to try and blur the difference, why?<br>
<br>
This war is the reflect of American Imperialism, try to turn off tv sometimes.<br>
<br>
Now i dont say that American Imperialism isnt in line with the winds of History, its just that im unhappy with it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hypocritical reasons, like i already said, elections soon, oil, geostrategy,Enron gate,  any reason i will accept it, but dont tell me again about bombings by Al Qaeda, that Irak has to do something with it.<br>
<br>
All this war will do is produce more terrorism and instability in an area where the balance is already weak.<br>
<br>
Btw, yes all western countries are helping each other to track real terrorism.(i said real, please take note)<br>
<br>
